the genuine fear of a Y2K computer crash that distracted us from premillennial fantasies
the transparency of the Internet and the power of hackers that made government secrecy seem less intimidating
hackers that made government secrecy seem less intimidating
millennial paranoids who made murder their therapy
Oliver Stone , Ross Perot and Johnnie Cochran
the last decade of the century
the lone gunman who murdered President John F. Kennedy
a parody of an elaborate government study
John Kenneth Galbraith -LRB- under a pseudonym -RRB- in The Washington Post

part of the late-century transformation of American paranoia
